On October 9, 2009, the White House released a statement by the Press Secretary announcing that President Obama had signed two bills into law. The first bill, H.R. 2131, reauthorized the United States Advisory Commission on Public Diplomacy and made amendments to the Foreign Affairs Reform and Restructuring Act of 1998. The second bill, H.R. 3593, amended the United States International Broadcasting Act of 1994 and extended the operation of Radio Free Asia for one year.